                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 128</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 8, Prime Minister <persName>Pholien</persName> arrived in Washington for
                    a scheduled meeting with <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Dean Acheson</persName> on
                    the following day. In the period since his arrival in New York with his wife on
                    March 27, he had visited the United Nations and dined with Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_AWR1">Austin</persName>, seen West Point, toured industrial
                    plants in Pittsburgh and Detroit, and viewed the installations and training
                    facilities at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base in Ohio, Connelly Air Force Base
                    in Texas where Belgian cadets were training, and Fort Benning Army installation
                    in Georgia.</p>
                <p>The Prime Minister’s proposed visit to the United States was first mentioned, and
                    favorably presented, in telegram 1400 from Brussels, February 28. Telegram 1435
                    from Brussels, March 6, added that it would be well if
                        <persName>Pholien</persName> could “visit industrial center Middle West
                    where he could obtain inspiration from size of our defense effort.” These
                    telegrams and other documents related to Departments of State and Defense
                    scheduling of this trip are in file 755.13.</p>
            </div>
